The Ethereals are amazing! Nebulob really adds depth to my songs when the tempo is right. However, Kazilleon is VERY off-key, so maybe you could re-tune the samples. Also, Rare Reedling sounds more like bagpipes rather than an accordion. Pummel seems to be more of a chromatic Monster, so the higher pitches should match that. It would also be helpful if there were either a setting that allows all or certain Monsters to have doubles due to long notes or place the long/short doubles next to each other. More octaves could also be implemented and there could be individual limits for which Monsters can have higher or lower notes. Pitch bend could be nice as well, as well as off-beat notes and short notes (you don't even need to re-record them; they'll just be cut off or sped up when a next note plays)
No flaws, no bugs, no issues whatsoever, this game is amazing.

Has good potential but I feel like a lot more could be added.... like an actualy way to change the tempo or some actual ways to have different rhythms that arent just the same eighth, quarter, half, and whole notes. content: Lack of updates shows the importance of this game to developers when people pay in order to play as opposed to being free. As mentioned before, this game is missing a lot of features. Namely on the musical side of things. It is impossible to do complex rhythmic sequences due in part to the simplistic approach to composing the music, triplets are impossible unless you want to give up on eighth notes and 16th notes. It could be very helpful to kinda emulate the app "Maestro: Composer", however that would mean a complete change to the game. Basically, this game was fun until a better composing app came out (considering the lack of composing apps that allow listening to what you write). I love this game and thank you for creating it, but here are a few things 
that you can get better: 1. Add more monsters in to the game. 2. Make more 
octaves in order for creating a bit more complicated music. 3. You can also 
add a more advanced mode of creating the melody. For example you can ask 
before creating a new music, does the person want to use easy mode or 
complicated one. 4. Make the piano have more buttons and octaves than it 
has right now. 5. If you want to make the game more popular, make it a bit 
cheaper right now, so people will want to buy it. Later on, you may 
increase the prices again (but not too much please). I think that for now 
this game is great, but there are still a lot of things to improve in order 
for it to become better, more functional and more interesting. For now, I 
give this game four stars. Thank you for reading this comment and I wish 
you good luck with making it a successful project.
